The paper proposes a new approach to 3D reconstruction and scene understanding using deep convolutional neural networks and auto-encoders. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with 3D geometry and navigation, which could place it in the graphics (cs.GR) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Finally, the paper makes use of synthetic data sets and proposes a new method for learning key geometric features, which could also place it in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
